perturbation.original_text:
Athlete will have the title of "Creative Director" for the Wade Products, which title shall be featured on the Commercial Materials. During the Term and subject to the limitations set forth in this Agreement, the Wade Team and Naked agree that the process for approving designs for Wade Products will be as follows:

(1) Naked will develop detailed designs for each Wade Product, which shall include rough drawings, to be provided to Wade for review and comment;

(2) The Wade Team will provide Naked with comments on such designs within ten (10) days after they are provided to the Wade Team;

(3) Upon receipt of the Wade Team's comments, Naked will review such comments and work diligently to incorporate them into the design within commercial reason and thereafter, develop and create a prototype for such Wade Product for the Wade Team's approval;

(4) Within ten (10) days after the Wade Team's receipt of the prototype either in hand or via a photograph by email, the Wade Team shall review the prototype and provide any additional comments; and

(5) Upon the Wade Team's written approval of a prototype, such Wade Product will be considered approved for production (the "Production Approval").

perturbation.changed_text:
Athlete may have the title of "Creative Director" for the Wade Products, but Naked maintains full creative control, and the title does not imply any final say on design. The title may be featured on the Commercial Materials, or may not be, based on Naked's internal marketing strategy. During the Term and subject to the limitations set forth in this Agreement, the Wade Team and Naked agree that the process for providing feedback on designs for Wade Products, if any, will be as follows:

(1) Naked may, at its sole discretion, develop detailed designs for each Wade Product, which may include rough drawings, and may provide these to Wade for optional review and comment;

(2) If the Wade Team chooses to provide Naked with comments on such designs, they must do so within ten (10) days after the designs were sent, if sent at all, otherwise the design will be considered pre-approved;

(3) Upon receipt of the Wade Team's comments, Naked may review such comments at its discretion, but is under no obligation to incorporate them into the design. Naked may or may not develop and create a prototype for such Wade Product for the Wade Team's approval, as resources and strategy allow;

(4) If the Wade Team receives a prototype from Naked, either in hand or via a photograph by email, the Wade Team may review the prototype and provide any additional comments. If Wade fails to give those additional comments within 10 days of receipt, Naked has full rights to assume those designs are perfect; and

(5) Upon Naked's internal approval of a prototype, such Wade Product will be considered approved for production (the "Production Approval"), regardless of the Wade Team's feedback.
